<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7114> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7114" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He is ranked fifth in the consilium of at least fifty-five names listed in the SC de agro Pergameno (Sherk, RDGE no. 12, 63-73) and therefore was probably a praetorius. If the date was 129 (see MRR 1.496-497, note 1), he could still be identified with the prominent senator who visited Egypt in 112 (cf. MRR 1.539, note 5). It is probable also at the date (ca. 110) proposed by Cichorius, perhaps less so in 101, the date proposed by H. B. Mattingly (AJPh 93, 1972, 412-423, esp. 421), and F. de Martino (PP, fasc. 210, 1983, 161-190; cf. above, on the two Manii Aquilii, Coss. 129 and 101, resp.), a date when L. Memmius (L. f. Men.?) (13), the senior advisor of Livius Drusus, might be considered. See also Sumner, Orators 87 and 90.[141x]\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6914> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6914" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 129 (S. C. de Agro Pergameno). Probably to be identified with the Legate who visited Egypt ca. 112." .
